main event: The observer watched a round, white object overhead that moved faster than any known aircraft at the time, maintained a steady course, and changed speed without clear data to draw a definite conclusion.
interesting points: The object was estimated to be at an altitude of approximately 10,000 feet.
The object appeared to deliberately maneuver, moving to a new location and staying near the observer's car for around 12 minutes.
The observer described the object as having a 'blaring siren' sound that went on and off for a second.
The observer tried to estimate the size of the object as being about 5,000 feet away.
The observer said the object was 'like a round die' in appearance when compared to a common object.
sighted object: a round, white object in the sky
